Document: VisualShaderNodeIf
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodeif.rst
Summary: Describes the VisualShaderNodeIf class, which compares two floating-point numbers and routes output based on the comparison result with tolerance.

- Port 1 and 2 provide the two floating-point numbers a and b that will be compared.
- Port 3 is the tolerance, which allows similar floating-point numbers to be considered equal.
- Port 4 is the output returned if a == b.
- Port 5 is the output returned if a > b.
- Port 6 is the output returned if a < b.